    {
      "question": "If the probability of an event $E$ occurring is $0.65$, what is the probability of the event 'not $E$'?",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Recall the property of complementary events: $P(E) + P(\\text{not } E) = 1$.",
          "Substitute the given value $P(E) = 0.65$.",
          "Solve for $P(\\text{not } E) = 1 - 0.65$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$P(\\bar{E}) = 1 - P(E) = 1 - 0.65 = 0.35$"
      },
